  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior/ M&E Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Execute on-site coordination and control of mechanical and electrical works to ensure timely and compliant project delivery.</li><li>Collaborate proactively with end user Points of Contact (PICs), subcontractors, and the site management team.</li><li>Lead site inspections and ensure that all M&E works comply with project specifications and regulations.</li><li>Monitor project progress and provide regular updates to stakeholders regarding timelines and potential issues.</li><li>Resolve any technical problems that arise during the construction process to maintain project momentum.</li><li>Prepare and review technical documentation, including drawings and specifications for M&E systems.</li><li>Ensure that all work is performed in accordance with health and safety regulations.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Building Services, Mechanical, or Electrical Engineering disciplines.</li><li>3-5 years of experience in building and construction projects, preferably in cleanroom, laboratory, or controlled environment-related projects.</li><li>Knowledge of mechanical and electrical systems, proficiency in relevant engineering software.</li></ul><p>If interested, please submit your application to cvs@jdawms.com with your expected salary and resume.</p><p>We regret that only short-listed candidates will be contacted shortly. By submitting your application or resume, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and sharing of your personal information with potential employers for their assessment.</p><p>JDA WMS Pte Ltd | EA Personnel: Pham Thi Tuyet Mai </p><p>EA License No: 23S1595 | EA Registration No: R25127838</p>",
